In C, you can initialize a char* (pointer to a character) to an empty string in a few different ways:
char* str = ""; strcpy(str, "");
char* str = strdup("");
char* str = (char*)malloc(1); str[0] = '\0';
char str[10] = {'\0'};
char c = "A"; // not allowed
char *c = "A"; // allowed
char c = 'A'; // allowed
